 | A-042 | 005FA generates portal activation/password-reset OTP challenges server-side, stores only OTP hashes, and records a pending communication-shell row without calling a real SMS/email provider. Tests use an explicit `PORTAL_AUTH_TEST_OTP` setting to simulate receipt. PAN/Aadhaar last-four verification currently compares against the stored encrypted-value placeholder strings because no decrypt/search adapter exists yet. | MP01/MP02 require OTP, but source docs do not specify a delivery provider and this sandbox has no network. Security docs forbid storing raw OTPs and sensitive values. The existing 003I communication shell is the source-compliant boundary until a provider adapter exists. | `docs/source/screen-spec-member-portal.md` MP01/MP02; `docs/source/security-privacy.md` §10 and sensitive-data list; `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` §5; `docs/slices/005FA-member-portal-authentication.md` | 005FA-member-portal-authentication and future notification/provider/security-hardening slices | High | Yes | 2026-07-09 | Replace placeholder last-four checks with a proper decrypt/hash-verification adapter when sensitive-value services exist; wire OTP delivery to the real notification provider when selected. |
 | A-043 | 005FB exposes `/api/v1/portal/produce-supply/` as an empty read-only shell with `source_status = model_not_implemented` until a `produce_supply_records` model/table is implemented. | `data-model.md` §11.6 defines the table, but the current Django members app has no corresponding model or migration. Inventing supply rows or deriving them from crop plans would create unsourced business data. | `docs/source/data-model.md` §11.6; `docs/source/screen-spec-member-portal.md` MP03/MP04 and permissions matrix; `docs/slices/005FB-member-portal-dashboard-profile-and-supply-view.md` | 005FB-member-portal-dashboard-profile-and-supply-view and future active-member/produce-supply slices | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-09 | Add the model-backed list and summary once the source-backed produce-supply persistence slice exists; until then the portal must show an empty state, not mock history. |
+| A-044 | 005G2 returns `401 INVALID_TOKEN` for old-token portal dashboard/profile/supply/application/password-change calls after the linked `PortalAccount` becomes suspended or inactive, rather than a portal-route-level `403`, because those routes use the shared session-bound bearer validator before portal scope is resolved. The validator revokes the session with reason `portal_account_status_changed`. | The slice allowed choosing exact route-level status by existing auth helper semantics, and the existing route stack authenticates the bearer session before route-specific permission checks. A single invalid-session boundary avoids exposing stale portal claims or own-data permissions. | `docs/slices/005G2-member-portal-session-and-audit-contract-hardening.md`; `docs/working/digests/epic-005-application-intake.md`; `docs/working/API_CONTRACTS.md` | 005G2-member-portal-session-and-audit-contract-hardening and future portal/staff route slices | Medium | No | 2026-07-10 | Implemented and tested for `/auth/me`, password change, portal own-data, and portal application routes. Staff/non-portal valid sessions still receive `403 PERMISSION_DENIED` on portal routes. |
